.\" Man page for ocode skills
.TH OCODE-SKILLS 1 "June 2025" "ocode" "User Commands"
.SH NAME
ocode-skills \- Manage skills
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B ocode skills
\fIsubcommand\fR [\fIargs\fR]
.SH DESCRIPTION
Manage ocode skills. Skills are markdown files that extend the agent's
capabilities with custom tools, prompts, and workflows.
.SH SUBCOMMANDS
.TP
\fBlist\fR, \fBls\fR
List bundled + installed skills.
.TP
\fBinstall\fR [\fIname\fR...]
Install bundled skills to ~/.config/opencode/skills/.
With no name arguments, installs all bundled skills.
.TP
\fBupgrade\fR, \fBupdate\fR [\fIname\fR...]
Install only when bundled content differs from installed.
With no name arguments, upgrades all bundled skills.
.TP
\fBuninstall\fR, \fBremove\fR \fIname\fR...
Remove an installed skill directory.
.TP
\fBhelp\fR, \fB\-h\fR, \fB\-\-help\fR
Show this help message and exit.
.SH EXAMPLES
.TP
List all skills:
.B ocode skills list
.TP
Install all bundled skills:
.B ocode skills install
.TP
Install specific skill:
.B ocode skills install my-skill
.TP
Upgrade all skills:
.B ocode skills upgrade
.TP
Uninstall a skill:
.B ocode skills uninstall my-skill
.SH FILES
.TP
\fI~/.config/opencode/skills/\fR
User-installed skills directory.
.SH SEE ALSO
.BR ocode (1)